---
description: Use when creating or modifying Hyde Park packages, package docs, package exports, packaging scripts, or release wiring.
globs:
  - "packages/**/package.json"
  - "packages/**/tsconfig.json"
  - "packages/**/tsup.config.ts"
  - "packages/**/src/**/*.ts"
  - "packages/**/test/**/*.ts"
  - "apps/docs/docs/packages/**/*.md"
  - "scripts/new-package.mjs"
  - "scripts/smoke/**/*.mjs"
alwaysApply: false
---

Follow Hyde Park package standards.

Codex Note:

- If this file was reached from `AGENTS.md`, treat it as the package-change routing rule for work that touches package structure, exports, docs pages, generator logic, or release wiring.
- For procedural steps, pair this rule with `.cursor/skills/add-package/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/skills/add-package-category/SKILL.md`, depending on the task.

Read first:

- `@docs/package-standards.md`
- `@docs/creating-packages.md`
- `@docs/release-guide.md`
- `@docs/workspace-structure.md`

Important package rules:

- Public packages must have a real scoped npm name and version.
- Public packages should expose `build`, `lint`, `typecheck`, `test`, and `clean` scripts.
- Public packages should publish `ESM + CJS + d.ts`.
- Public packages should use explicit `exports`.
- Workspace dependencies should use `workspace:*`.
- Public package docs should be added under `apps/docs/docs/packages/<category>/`.
- If a package has unusual packaging behavior, update `scripts/smoke/consumer-smoke.mjs`.

When adding a new package category:

- decide the naming rule
- add the docs folder
- update `apps/docs/docs/.vitepress/config.ts`
- update maintainer docs in `docs/`
- decide whether `scripts/new-package.mjs` should support the category

Do not treat the umbrella package as a replacement for leaf packages.
